data.title: Business
data.meta_description:
Botany - Free ebook download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read book online for free. The document appears to be the yearbook for 2017 of the Indian Association for Angiosperm Taxonomy (IAAT). Some key details:

- IAAT is a society registered under the Societies Registration Act of 1860, with the aim of promoting the science of Angiosperm taxonomy in India. 

- The yearbook provides information on the bye-laws, executive council members for 2015-2017, past office bearers, annual conferences held, medals awarded, fellows and life members of IAAT. 

- Membership of IAAT is open to those interested in Angiosperm Taxonomy, with categories including patron, honorary, life, ordinary and student members. Subscription fees and eligibility criteria are provided
